The force field above the beach blocks access to the enemy base at the top of the hill. Find the force field power control and blast it to bits.
The Base's Command Post is connected to a series of SAM sites. By destroying those connections, you can expose the Command Post core. Hit the core hard.
Fight off the forces that protect the rocket silos. Then, target the control panels before the rockets launch. Your efforts will keep the resistance alive.
Move on to the VTOL landing pad and guide the BFT into the cargo hold. The aircraft will transport you to the next campaign.
Break into the Network lab. Fight off the security and refit the BFT with new technology. Then, you can reach enemy operations on the other side of the canyon.
The best way to weaken enemy forces is to destroy the main power supply. Blast through the Power Plant complex, then obliterate the core.
Machines extract ore for weapon production from the mine pit. By destroying the digging devices in the pit, you'll be closer to drowning out the Network's efforts.
The foundry is the heart of the Network's weapon production operation. Bust through its defenses and break it down with a barrage of BFT firepower!
A VTOL is on the way. Proceed to helipad for transport to the next area. If you've hit the bridge switch in the foundry, you'll be able to cross over to the pick up area.
The volcano is in a huge crater that is protected by Network forces. Your first mission is to fight off the complex's exterior defenses and enter the main crater.
A Lava pool blocks the bridge near two large craters. By destroying the pumps that fill the pool, you can drain the lava and clear the way.
Make your way to the hovertank plant east of the volcano and put the BFT on the production line. Once you have the technology, you can sail smoothly to the volcano.
Cross the lava to the volcano entrance and destroy the forces that block the entrance tunnel. Then, enter the volcano and keep blasting.
The TNT Beam is in the volcano crater. Fight your way to the top. Then, target the beam. Its weak point is in the center. Avoid the lasers and attack.
Get to the VTOL pad before the entire complex is swimming in lava!
The machines are making chemical weapons. The first step is to cut off their water supply. Destroy the flood gates of the main dam and let the water flow.
The missile construction facility provides lift for the machine's chemical weapons. Take it out before the missiles are complete.
The chemical production plant is volatile. With the right firepower, in the right places, you can bury it for good.
Reports show that the machines are constructing a secret weapon under the courtyard ruins. Find it and put an end to this new threat.
Now that the chemical threat is over, you can make your escape. Go to the VTOL landing site for pickup.
Access to enemy operations under the ice is blocked by a communications center. Knock out the enemy installation, then make your way under the icy surface.
A new batch is about to be shipped to the network's clone city. Work your way to the shipping entrance of the facility and destroy the clones.
Enemy operations are largely underwater. Go to the sub production facility and refit the BFT so that you can dive deep and destroy the underwater installations.
The machines get energy by extracting heat from the ocean floor. Dive down and place remote mines in the geo-thermal power plant's vents.
The way to enter the manufacturing plant is through underwater tunnels. Dive deep, cut through the ice cave and take apart the machine.
M6: Go to VTOL Landing Area
You've destroyed all cloning operations. Proceed to the VTOL landing area for pick up.
The network is building a city underground. Fight your way to the elevator that leads to the construction site.
Sensors show that the network's central core is powered by three remote power stations. You can reach them through transporters.
Hover over the hot stuff, then track down the power plant and unplug it.
Access to the final power station is through an underwater passage. Switch to sub mode and dive.
With all of the power stations offline, the central core of the network is exposed. Hit it with all of your power and crash the system.
* Must restart campaign before change takes effect
